Consider the following recursive C function.
void get(int n) {
    if (n < 1) return;
    get(n-1);
    get(n-3);
    printf("%d", n);
}
If get(5) function is being called in main() then how many times will the get() function be invoked before returning to the main()?
A. 15
B. 25
C. 35
D. 45

