sourceQuestion:
Consider the following ANSI C program:

#include <stdio.h>
int foo(int x, int y, int q) {
    if ((x <= 0) && (y <= 0))
        return q;
    if (x <= 0)
        return foo(x, y - q, q);
    if (y <= 0)
        return foo(x - q, y, q);
    return foo(x, y - q, q) + foo(x - q, y, q);
}
int main() {
    int p = foo(10, 15, 10);
    printf("%d", p);
    return 0;
}

The output of the program upon execution is _______.

A. 10
B. 20
C. 30
D. 40

